# winget software

# open the terminal and set the default profile to "Windows PowerShell", but run this command with "Command Prompt"
winget install Bitwarden.Bitwarden && winget install eloston.ungoogled-chromium && winget install Discord.Discord && winget install rcmaehl.MSEdgeRedirect && winget install EpicGames.EpicGamesLauncher && winget install Balena.Etcher && winget install flux.flux && winget install GnuPG.GnuPG && winget install Jackett.Jackett && winget install Joplin.Joplin && winget install LibreWolf.LibreWolf && winget install NordVPN.NordVPN && winget install qBittorrent.qBittorrent && winget install Valve.Steam && winget install TorProject.TorBrowser && winget install Ubisoft.Connect && winget install VideoLan.VLC





# software from internet

AMD Website -> Drivers & Support -> Auto-Detect





# config

  # if dual booting with another os, you need to configure windows to use UTC time, this is so the clock stays correct when switching between os's
    - you can do this on windows by running the following command from an admin command prompt...
        - reg add "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\TimeZoneInformation" /v RealTimeIsUniversal /d 1 /t REG_DWORD /f
  
  
  # qBittorrent
    - in preferences, configure power management, enable anonymous mode, and recheck torrents on completion
    - "View" tab -> Search Engine
    - configure search by...
        - jackett was already installed through winget, but you still need to open it and allow it to run on boot, and install and set up the jackett plugin
        - to install the jackett plugin, go to the qbittorrent/search-plugins repository on GitHub -> How to configure jackett plugin -> download the plugin to a temporary location and read the rest of the page to set up
        - in qbittorrent open the "Search" tab -> search plugins -> install a new one -> import the downloaded file -> delete the plugin saved to temporary location
        - to configure jackett, open the url that is displayed in qBittorrent -> Search tab -> search plugins

    
  # Chromium
    - config in Bitwarden
